title.rendered: NEWTECONS ACCOMPLISHED THE TOPPING-OUT CEREMONY OF SORA GARDENS II PROJECT

content.rendered:
(Binh Duong, September 30, 2020) Newtecons Investment Construction Joint Stock Company coordinated with Japanese BTMJR Investment Company Limited for a successful topping-out ceremony of Sora Gardens II Project. The ceremony honourably received the attendance of Becamex Tokyu’s Leadership representatives, BTMJR Investment Company, Mitsubishi Estate Group, Newtecons’ Leadership and all staff members of parties engaged in the project.

Representatives of the Owner, Consultant and General Contractor cheered for the successful topping-out of the project

Sora Gardens II is built right next to Sora Garden I in Binh Duong Province. This 24-storey and 1-attic high-rise condominium involves Newtecons as the General Contractor and has a gross floor area of up to 90,000m2.

In his speech at the ceremony, Mr. Onuma Minoru – Deputy General Director of Becamex Tokyu – praised the efforts of Newtecons and construction units. He believes that Newtecons, who dedicated more than 1,300 thousand hours of safe working, will hold themselves up to bring residents with a perfect Japanese-quality living space.

Mr. Onuma Minoru – Deputy General Director of Becamex Tokyu spoke at the ceremony

Mr. Hoang Phuong Lam – CEO of Newtecons delivered thanks for the trust of the Owner and partnership of construction units who had been side by side with Newtecons to overcome challenges and reached the today success. Newtecons committed to greater efforts for the project accomplishment.

Mr. Hoang Phuong Lam – Newtecons CEO spoke at the ceremony

This event is, among others, a proof for the prestige and position of Newtecons. We are confident to meet the strict standards of domestic and foreign Owners.

After the ceremony, Newtecons’ Site Management Board eagerly started off the finishing work to ensure the hand-over schedule in early 2021.
